  7→<!--
  8→  Reference template for the visual-explainer skill: data tables.
  9→  Rose/cranberry palette — distinctly different from terracotta (architecture)
 10→  and teal (mermaid) templates so agents absorb variety.
 11→  Key patterns demonstrated:
 12→  - Rose/cranberry palette (NOT indigo/violet)
 13→  - KPI summary cards above the table (visual hook before the data)
 14→  - Collapsible <details> section (replaces static callout)
 15→  - Depth tiers: elevated KPIs, default table, collapsible for secondary
 16→  - Real <table> element with sticky header, alternating rows
 17→  - Status indicator badges (match, gap, partial)
 18→  - Text wrapping in wide columns, code references in cells
 19→  - Summary footer row with aggregate status
 20→  - Staggered row animation via --i variable
 21→  - Both light and dark themes via prefers-color-scheme
 22→  - Responsive horizontal scroll wrapper
 23→-->
