  7→<!--
  8→  Reference template for the visual-explainer skill: Mermaid diagrams.
  9→  Teal/cyan palette — distinctly different from terracotta (architecture)
 10→  and rose (data-table) templates so agents absorb variety.
 11→  Key patterns demonstrated:
 12→  - Teal/cyan palette (NOT indigo/violet)
 13→  - Dot-grid background atmosphere (different from radial gradient)
 14→  - Large heading (38px) for typographic contrast
 15→  - ESM import of Mermaid + @mermaid-js/layout-elk
 16→  - Mermaid theme: 'base' + full themeVariables, fontSize: 16px
 17→  - CSS overrides: .nodeLabel 16px, .edgeLabel 13px
 18→  - look: 'classic' for clean lines
